# Agent playbook — bundle release and sync (local only)

Copy to **`AGENTS-LOCAL.md`** in the bundle root. This file is gitignored. Do not commit it.

## When to use this playbook

Engage when the user asks to:

- Release or version the bundle (e.g. “bump version”, “prepare v1.0.0”, “update changelog”)
- Cut a git tag for cursor-dev-workflows
- Classify pending bundle changes for semver

For normal workflow routing in this repo, use [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) and [which-workflow.md](which-workflow.md) instead.

## Read order

1. [docs/versioning.md](docs/versioning.md) — MAJOR / MINOR / PATCH rules
2. [CHANGELOG.md](CHANGELOG.md) — `## [Unreleased]` section
3. [VERSION](VERSION) — current released version
4. Git diff / status — classify all pending bundle changes

## Edit rules

- Add user-facing notes under `## [Unreleased]` in [CHANGELOG.md](CHANGELOG.md)
- For **MAJOR** changes, include an **Adopter action** subsection (bulleted list)
- Update [VERSION](VERSION) only when cutting a release (not for every doc edit)
- Never stage or commit `MAINTAINER.md`, `AGENTS-LOCAL.md`, or machine-specific paths

## Suggested commit plan (user must explicitly ask to commit)

1. `docs(changelog): note <summary>` — changelog-only updates before release
2. `chore(release): mark bundle vX.Y.Z` — final VERSION + dated changelog section

One logical change per commit per [docs/workflows/commits-logical-order.md](docs/workflows/commits-logical-order.md).

## Tagging (only when user asks)

```bash
git tag -a vX.Y.Z -m "cursor-dev-workflows vX.Y.Z"
```

Do not push unless the user explicitly asks. Do not amend, squash, or use `--no-verify` unless requested.

## Release steps

1. Ensure restructure / pending work is on `main` (or user’s release branch)
2. Finalize `## [Unreleased]` → `## [X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD`
3. Set [VERSION](VERSION) to `X.Y.Z`
4. Commit when asked
5. Annotated tag `vX.Y.Z` when asked
6. Remind maintainer to notify adopters on **MAJOR** bumps (see [MAINTAINER.md.example](MAINTAINER.md.example))

## Boundaries

- **Docs-only repo** — no `TEST_COMMAND` runs required for bundle releases
- Do not duplicate full release steps into tracked [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md)
- Read gitignored [MAINTAINER.md](MAINTAINER.md) if present for org-specific sync mapping
